# Atlas CertOps
## Standard Operating Procedures (SOP) Manual

Version 1.0

---

# Purpose

The Atlas CertOps SOP Manual establishes standardized operational procedures for all certificate lifecycle activities.

These procedures ensure consistency, repeatability, accountability, and audit readiness across the organization.

---

# SOP-001
## Create Certificate

### Purpose

Create a new certificate record.

### Responsible Roles

Operator

Compliance Manager

Administrator

### Prerequisites

• Appropriate permissions
• Required certificate information available

### Procedure

1. Navigate to Certificates.
2. Select New Certificate.
3. Complete all required fields.
4. Upload supporting documentation.
5. Verify owner assignment.
6. Verify expiration date.
7. Save record.

### Verification

• Certificate appears in inventory.
• Audit record created.
• Notifications generated if applicable.

---

# SOP-002
## Renew Certificate

Purpose

Replace an expiring certificate.

Procedure

1. Locate certificate.
2. Select Renew.
3. Upload replacement certificate.
4. Update issue date.
5. Update expiration date.
6. Submit.

Verification

• Old revision retained.
• New revision active.
• Audit history preserved.

---

# SOP-003
## Approve Certificate

1. Open Pending Approvals.
2. Review attached documentation.
3. Validate information.
4. Approve or Reject.
5. Enter comments if required.

---

# SOP-004
## Reject Certificate

Reasons may include:

Missing documentation

Expired documentation

Incorrect owner

Invalid issuer

Duplicate submission

Rejected certificates return to submitter.

